Class Rochambeau

  • java.lang.Object
    • Rochambeau

  • public class Rochambeau
extends java.lang.Object
    Class to model the game of Rochambeau. All methods of this class are static. Instances of this class should not be created (thus you don't need a constructor).

      • getWinner

        public static int getWinner(int throw1,
            int throw2)
        Determine the winner, given two Rochambeau "throws".
        Parameters:
        throw1 - The throw of player 1, Must be 0, 1, or 2.
        throw2 - The throw of player 2, Must be 0, 1, or 2.
        Returns:
        1 if throw 1 wins
        -1 if throw 2 wins
        0 if there is a tie
